subSubSection.paragraph:
Tagami (2011
, 
2014
) gave it the Japanese name “Shizuoka-kohige-kurobane-kinokobae”. We assume that it includes most of black fungus gnats which have been called locally as Japanese “kobae” [= gnats] (
Tajimi City 2020
), “tajimimushi” [= gnats of Tajimi City], and “kurobane-kinokobae” [= sciarids] (
Goto 2014
) in Tajimi City.
